SOQL:

*)Aggregate query: Object->Contact
				
				Query:	
				select count(id)total,AccountId, account.name  from contact where AccountId != null group by AccountId ,account.name
	
				Notes:
				1. Grouping require for arrange total count for each parent record.
				2. Aggregate works in child object only, cause parent does't have any child field for grouping.
				
*)Group by: Object->Contact
		
				Query:
				select firstname,lastname from contact group by firstname,lastname
				select count(Id),firatname from contact group by firstname
				select count(name) we can write field name also
				
				Notes:
				1.when we want to get unique records
				2.we must declare fields in groupby what we declare in select

*)Order by: Object->Contact
			
				Query
				ascending:
				select firstname,lastname from contact order by firstname
				descending:
				select firstname,lastname from contact order by firstname DESC
				
				Note:
				1.when we want data in ascending,descending manner
			
*)Group by and order by together: Object->Contact
				
				Query:
				select firstname from contact group by firstname order by firstname

*)RecordType:
				Query:
				
				1>. List<RecordType> allRecordType =  [Select Name, Id From RecordType where sObjectType='account' and isActive=true];	
				2>. Id test1RecId = Schema.SObjectType.account.getRecordTypeInfosByName().get('test1').getRecordTypeId();

*)All Fields:
				Query:
				1>. select fields(all) from account limit 200
				

*)Apex class:
				Query:
				1>. Select Name From Apexclass order by createddate desc
				
*)Objects Fields:
				Query:
				1>. SELECT QualifiedApiName, Label, DeveloperName, Description, DataType, ExtraTypeInfo,  Length, Precision, Scale FROM FieldDefinition WHERE EntityDefinition.QualifiedApiName = 'account'	

*)Find listof All Objects: 
					
				query:
				1>. SELECT fields(all) FROM EntityDefinition where PluralLabel   like '%Zone%' limit 200
				
*)Find List of relatedName:	
				
				query:
				1>. select id,name,description,website from account where name In ('temp-28','temp-27')
				
*)SOSL:
			query:		
				1>. List<List<SObject>> searchList = [FIND 'SFDC' IN ALL FIELDS RETURNING Account(Name), Contact(FirstName,LastName)];
				
wire: instante or repeate kind of data we use wire (not mendatory we neee)

